msgctxt "sn22.81:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.81:0.2"
msgid "8. Khajjanīyavagga "
msgstr "8. Itchy "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 81. Pālileyyasutta → pārileyyakasuttaṃ (bj) | pārileyya (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.81:0.3"
msgid "81. Pālileyyasutta "
msgstr "81. At Pārileyya "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.95, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.81:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.81:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya kosambiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Kosambi for alms. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:1.3"
msgid "Kosambiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto sāmaṃ senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya anāmantetvā upaṭṭhāke anapaloketvā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ eko adutiyo cārikaṃ pakkāmi. "
msgstr "After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he set his lodgings in order himself. Taking his bowl and robe, without informing his attendants or taking leave of the mendicant Saṅgha, he set out to go wandering alone, with no companion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.81:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu acirapakkantassa bhagavato yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then, not long after the Buddha had left, one of the mendicants went to Venerable Ānanda and told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:2.2"
msgid "“esāvuso ānanda, bhagavā sāmaṃ senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya anāmantetvā upaṭṭhāke anapaloketvā bhikkhusaṅghaṃ eko adutiyo cārikaṃ pakkanto”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.81:2.3"
msgid "“Yasmiṃ, āvuso, samaye bhagavā sāmaṃ senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya anāmantetvā upaṭṭhāke anapaloketvā bhikkhusaṅghaṃ eko adutiyo cārikaṃ pakkamati, ekova bhagavā tasmiṃ samaye viharitukāmo hoti; "
msgstr "Ānanda said, “Reverend, when the Buddha leaves like this it means he wants to stay alone. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:2.4"
msgid "na bhagavā tasmiṃ samaye kenaci anubandhitabbo hotī”ti. "
msgstr "At this time no-one should follow him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: pālileyyakaṃ → pārileyyakaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.81:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena pālileyyakaṃ tadavasari. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, traveling stage by stage, arrived at Pārileyya, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:3.2"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā pālileyyake viharati bhaddasālamūle. "
msgstr "where he stayed at the root of a sacred sal tree. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then several mendicants went up to Venerable Ānanda and exchanged greetings with him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.81:3.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side and said to him, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:3.5"
msgid "“cirassutā kho no, āvuso ānanda, bhagavato sammukhā dhammī kathā; "
msgstr "“Reverend, it’s been a long time since we’ve heard a Dhamma talk from the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:3.6"
msgid "icchāma mayaṃ, āvuso ānanda, bhagavato sammukhā dhammiṃ kathaṃ sotun”ti. "
msgstr "We wish to hear a Dhamma talk from the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.96, sc4
msgctxt "sn22.81:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando tehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena pālileyyakaṃ bhaddasālamūlaṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda together with those mendicants went to Pārileyya to see the Buddha. They bowed and sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi. "
msgstr "and the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired them with a Dhamma talk. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.81:4.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Now at that time one of the monks had the thought, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.4"
msgid "“kathaṃ nu kho jānato kathaṃ passato anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hotī”ti? "
msgstr "“How do you know and see in order to end the defilements in the present life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.81:4.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tassa bhikkhuno cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing what that monk was thinking, addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.81:4.6"
msgid "“vicayaso desito, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I’ve taught the Dhamma analytically. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.7"
msgid "vicayaso desitā cattāro satipaṭṭhānā; "
msgstr "I’ve analytically taught the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.8"
msgid "vicayaso desitā cattāro sammappadhānā; "
msgstr "the four right efforts, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.9"
msgid "vicayaso desitā cattāro iddhipādā; "
msgstr "the four bases of psychic power, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.10"
msgid "vicayaso desitāni pañcindriyāni; "
msgstr "the five faculties, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.11"
msgid "vicayaso desitāni pañca balāni; "
msgstr "the five powers, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.12"
msgid "vicayaso desitā sattabojjhaṅgā; "
msgstr "the seven awakening factors, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.13"
msgid "vicayaso desito ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo. "
msgstr "and the noble eightfold path. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.14"
msgid "Evaṃ vicayaso desito, bhikkhave, mayā dhammo. "
msgstr "That’s how I’ve taught the Dhamma analytically. "

# NOTE: Contra BB, I read this as a locative absolute. The context, and the panidhekaccassa, suggest the sense of “though, despite”. It seems a bit harsh, but I guess the Buddha was in a bad mood. Unless we take this sense, the structure of the Buddha’s answer is hard to account for.
msgctxt "sn22.81:4.15"
msgid "Evaṃ vicayaso desite kho, bhikkhave, mayā dhamme atha ca panidhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Though I’ve taught the Dhamma analytically, still a certain mendicant present here has this thought: "

msgctxt "sn22.81:4.16"
msgid "‘kathaṃ nu kho jānato kathaṃ passato anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hotī’ti? "
msgstr "‘How do you know and see in order to end the defilements in the present life?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.97, sc5
msgctxt "sn22.81:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, jānato kathaṃ passato anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti? "
msgstr "And how, mendicants, do you know and see in order to end the defilements in the present life? "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.2"
msgid "Idha bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto "
msgstr "Take an uneducated ordinary person who has not seen the noble ones, and is neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.81:5.3"
msgid "rūpaṃ attato samanupassati. "
msgstr "They regard form as self. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.4"
msgid "Yā kho pana sā, bhikkhave, samanupassanā saṅkhāro so. "
msgstr "But that regarding is just a conditioned phenomenon. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.5"
msgid "So pana saṅkhāro kiṃnidāno kiṃsamudayo kiṃjātiko kiṃpabhavo? "
msgstr "And what’s the source, origin, birthplace, and root of that conditioned phenomenon? "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.6"
msgid "Avijjāsamphassajena, bhikkhave, vedayitena phuṭṭhassa assutavato puthujjanassa uppannā taṇhā; "
msgstr "When an uneducated ordinary person is struck by feelings born of contact with ignorance, craving arises. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.7"
msgid "tatojo so saṅkhāro. "
msgstr "That conditioned phenomenon is born from that. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.8"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, sopi saṅkhāro anicco saṅkhato paṭiccasamuppanno. "
msgstr "So that conditioned phenomenon is impermanent, conditioned, and dependently originated. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.9"
msgid "Sāpi taṇhā aniccā saṅkhatā paṭiccasamuppannā. "
msgstr "And that craving, "

# NOTE: The syntax here suggests that vedana and phassa are to be taken together. But the later passages show that this is just an artifact of abbreviation.
msgctxt "sn22.81:5.10"
msgid "Sāpi vedanā, sopi phasso anicco saṅkhato paṭiccasamuppanno. "
msgstr "that feeling, that contact, "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.11"
msgid "Sāpi avijjā aniccā saṅkhatā paṭiccasamuppannā. "
msgstr "and that ignorance are also impermanent, conditioned, and dependently originated. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:5.12"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, jānato evaṃ passato anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should know and see in order to end the defilements in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.81:6.1"
msgid "Na heva kho rūpaṃ attato samanupassati; "
msgstr "Perhaps they don’t regard form as self, "

