msgid "api ca kho evaṃdiṭṭhi hoti: "
msgstr "Still, they have such a view: "

# NOTE: This kind of double demonstrative construction is an emphatic identity. This is in fact the Upanishadic thesis.
msgctxt "sn22.81:10.7"
msgid "‘so attā so loko, so pecca bhavissāmi nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo’ti. "
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are one and the same. After passing away I will be permanent, everlasting, eternal, and imperishable.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.81:10.8"
msgid "Yā kho pana sā, bhikkhave, sassatadiṭṭhi saṅkhāro so. "
msgstr "But that eternalist view is just a conditioned phenomenon. "

msgctxt "sn22.81:10.9"
msgid "So pana saṅkhāro kiṃnidāno … pe … "
msgstr "And what’s the source of that conditioned phenomenon? … "

msgctxt "sn22.81:10.10"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, jānato evaṃ passato anantarā āsavānaṃ khayo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should know and see in order to end the defilements in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.99, sc11
msgctxt "sn22.81:11.1"
msgid "Na heva kho rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, "
msgstr "Perhaps they don’t regard form "

msgctxt "sn22.81:11.2"
msgid "na vedanaṃ … "
msgstr "or feeling "

msgctxt "sn22.81:11.3"
msgid "na saññaṃ … "
msgstr "or perception "

